    • findByActiveToDateGreaterThanEqualOrderByName

      List<Security> findByActiveToDateGreaterThanEqualOrderByName(String dateString) throws ParseException
      Finds securities that are active on or after the specified date, also includes the private instruments. They are sorted by name.
      Parameters:
      dateString - The date string (YYYY-MM-DD) to filter active securities.
      Returns:
      A list of active securities.
      Throws:
      ParseException - If the dateString cannot be parsed.

    • tryUpToIntradayDataWhenRetryIntraLoadGreaterThan0

      List<Security> tryUpToIntradayDataWhenRetryIntraLoadGreaterThan0(Integer idTenant, Integer idWatchlist)
      Attempts to update the intraday data for securities in a specific watchlist, whereby the number of failed intraday loads must be greater than 0. The user could trigger this action to force an intraday update of a previously unsuccessful update.
      Parameters:
      idTenant - The tenant's ID, for security reasons.
      idWatchlist - The ID of the watchlist.
      Returns:
      A list of securities for which intraday data update was attempted.

    • tryUpToDateHistoricalDataWhenRetryHistoryLoadGreaterThan0

      List<Security> tryUpToDateHistoricalDataWhenRetryHistoryLoadGreaterThan0(Integer idTenant, Integer idWatchlist)
      Attempts to update the historical price data for securities in a specific watchlist, where the number of failed historical loads must be greater than 0. The user could trigger this action to force a historical price data update of a previously unsuccessful update.
      Parameters:
      idTenant - The tenant's ID, for security reasons.
      idWatchlist - The ID of the watchlist.
      Returns:
      A list of securities for which historical data update was attempted.

    • searchBuilderWithExclusion

      List<Security> searchBuilderWithExclusion(Integer idWatchlist, Integer idCorrelationSet, SecuritycurrencySearch securitycurrencySearch, Integer idTenant)
      Searches for securities based on criteria, excluding those in a given watchlist or correlation set. It is intended, for example, to expand a correlation set or watch list with additional instruments. Therefore, existing instruments may no longer appear in the selection.
      Parameters:
      idWatchlist - ID of the watchlist whose existing instruments are no longer offered
      idCorrelationSet - ID of the correlation set whose existing instruments are no longer offered
      securitycurrencySearch - The search criteria.
      idTenant - The ID of the tenant, for safety reasons.
      Returns:
      A list of securities matching the criteria.

      summarySecurityMap - A map containing the calculations for each individual security, which will be updated.
      Returns:

    • reloadAsyncFullHistoryquote

      void reloadAsyncFullHistoryquote(Security securitycurrency)

      Parameters:

    • reloadAsyncFullHistoryquoteExternal

      void reloadAsyncFullHistoryquoteExternal(Integer idSecuritycurrency)

      Parameters:
      idSecuritycurrency - The ID of the security/currency pair.

    • getDataProviderResponseForUser

      String getDataProviderResponseForUser(Integer idSecuritycurrency, boolean isIntraday)
      The user interface receives a link to check the price data provider of a security. If an API key is required, only the backend can evaluate this link and return the corresponding content. The content of the provider may also be determined in the backend for other reasons.
      Parameters:
      idSecuritycurrency - The ID of the security.
      isIntraday - True if intraday data is requested, false for historical data.
      Returns:
      The raw response string from the data provider.

      Parameters:

      isIntraday - True if intraday data is requested, false for historical data.
      Returns:
      The URL string for the data provider.

      Checks if a user has the permission to change derived fields of a security. These properties include the basic instrument, the formula and the additional instruments.

    • setDividendDownloadLink

      void setDividendDownloadLink(SecuritycurrencyPosition<Security> securitycurrencyPosition)
      Sets the appropriate download link for dividend data on the securitycurrencyPosition. If a dividend data connector is configured for the security and requires an API key that the current context may not provide directly to the frontend, this method sets a backend-redirect URL. Otherwise, it attempts to set a direct URL to the dividend data provider. The link is set on the dividendUrl property of the securitycurrencyPosition.
      Parameters:
      securitycurrencyPosition - The security position object on which the dividend download URL should be set.

    • setSplitDownloadLink

      void setSplitDownloadLink(SecuritycurrencyPosition<Security> securitycurrencyPosition)
      Sets the appropriate download link for stock split data on the securitycurrencyPosition. If a split data connector is configured for the security and requires an API key that the current context may not provide directly to the frontend, this method sets a backend-redirect URL. Otherwise, it attempts to set a direct URL to the split data provider. The link is set on the splitUrl property of the securitycurrencyPosition.
      Parameters:
      securitycurrencyPosition - The security position object on which the split download URL should be set.
